ers</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, as well as the latest <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.creative.com">SB Live drivers</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->?  Updating dribers usually solves such issues.<br>
<br>
ACPI is the reason your IRQ's are being shared and it occurs by default in W2K and XP.  It shouldn't cause issues with modern hardware/drivers, although there have been issues with Creative sound cards and VIA chipsets, almost entirely because Creative drivers suck.  Still, most people use this combo without issue.<br>
<br>
Turning off ACPI without reinstalling the OS can cause further issues and is not recommended.  Before you do so, you can also try physically moving your PCI cards around to change the (hardware) interupt line that the card uses. (which has nothing to do with the irq that is assigned.)  Avoid using the PCI slot under the AGP slot. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=takkl>takkl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 44<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/24/02 8:30:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3492.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> via latency patch <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daerv>Daerv</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 271<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(11/25/02 12:07:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3492.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Well I installed the latest 4 in 1's last night which were the only things I'd forgotten. Played today and no lock ups in about 7 hours so its all good <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> . <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=28162" target="top">Daerv Heroe</a><